Types of License

			    License Types


    There are three major classes of license:  Capabilities, pseudo-license
    and frame-license.  Capabilites determine what a user may or may not do
    while running SETOP and OPPS.  Pseudo-license is used by various system
    utility programs to determine what a user may or may not do while running
    each of the various utility programs.  Frame-license may be set, enabled
    or disabled on the users frame (or job) so that the operating system may
    determine what capabilities the user has while running various programs.
    Frame-license also controls what access a user has to user and system
    information on each host.

